article.headline: Nebraska 81, Florida A&amp,M 56
article.story: LINCOLN, Neb. -- Sek Henry scored a season-high 19 points to lead three Nebraska players in double figures, and the Cornhuskers finished nonconference play with a 81-56 victory over Florida A&M on Monday night. Cookie Miller and Henry hit 3-pointers to put Nebraska up 27-13 with 7 minutes left in the first half, and the Huskers never led by fewer than 12 points the rest of the way. Steve Harley added 15 points and Paul Velander had 12, and the Huskers (10-3) shot 57 percent from the field. Nebraska held a 37-23 rebounding advantage.. Dale Hughes made 6-of-8 3-pointers and led the Rattlers (2-10) with 20 points. Joe Ballard had 14. Nebraska has held all 13 of its opponents under 67 points this season, the first Husker squad to do so since 1981-82.
